According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Electric Rubber Gloves Market was valued at USD 1.05 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 1.12 billion in 2026 to USD 1.85 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 6.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth due to stringent workplace safety regulations, increasing investments in electrical infrastructure, and rising awareness regarding personal protective equipment (PPE) across industries. Electric rubber gloves, designed to protect workers from electrical hazards, are becoming indispensable in utilities, manufacturing, construction, automotive, and renewable energy sectors. Advancements in dielectric materials, improved glove durability, and enhanced comfort are further supporting widespread adoption worldwide.
